com.guardtime.ksi.service.ha

Class SigningHAService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guardtime.ksi.service.ha.SigningHAService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KSISigningService, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class SigningHAService
extends Object
implements KSISigningService
    KSI Signing Service which combines clients to achieve redundancy. NB! It is highly recommended that all the aggregator configurations would be in sync with each other (except credentials), but if this is not the case then the configurations will be consolidated in an optimistic manner which means that if a configuration parameter would improve how user can consume the service then it's preferred in the consolidated configuration.

      • sign

        public Future<AggregationResponse> sign(DataHash dataHash,
                                        Long level)
                                 throws KSIException
        Creates a non-blocking signing request. Sends the request to all the subservices in parallel. First successful response is used, others are cancelled. Request fails only if all the subservices fail.
        Specified by:
        sign in interface KSISigningService
        Parameters:
        dataHash - instance of DataHash to be signed.
        level - the dataHash's level in the local aggregation tree.
        Returns:
        Instance of AggregationResponseFuture containing Aggregation response data.
        Throws:
        KSIException - in case any error occurs.
        See Also:
        KSISigningService.sign(DataHash, Long)

      • registerAggregatorConfigurationListener

        public void registerAggregatorConfigurationListener(ConfigurationListener<AggregatorConfiguration> listener)
        Registers configuration listeners that will be called if this SigningHAService's configuration changes. They will not be called if subservice's configuration changes in a way that does not change the consolidated configuration. To get detailed info about subservices' configurations one should register their own listeners directly on subservices. Listener will be called instantaneously once with the latest consolidation result as part of the registration if the latest result is not null.
        Specified by:
        registerAggregatorConfigurationListener in interface KSISigningService
        Parameters:
        listener - may not be null.

      • getAggregationConfiguration

        public Future<AggregatorConfiguration> getAggregationConfiguration()
        Invokes a configuration for all the subservices. Does not block until responses are received. Active configuration listeners are only called if any of the responses change the state of consolidated configuration.
        Specified by:
        getAggregationConfiguration in interface KSISigningService
        Returns:
        A future of the result. Can be used as an alternative to listeners to access the configuration result.
